---
import AboutHeroImage from '../assets/blog-placeholder-about.jpg';
import { loadAppConfig } from '../config/load-app-config';
import Layout from '../layouts/BlogPost.astro';

const app = loadAppConfig('maxxing-ai');
const supportEmail = app.supportEmail?.[0] ?? 'support@mail.finoai.net';
const supportMailto = `mailto:${supportEmail}?subject=${encodeURIComponent(
	`${app.name} Support Request`,
)}`;
---

<Layout
	title={`About ${app.name}`}
	description={`${app.name} helps people use AI thoughtfully while keeping support, privacy, and subscription information easy to find.`}
	pubDate={new Date('June 21 2026')}
	heroImage={AboutHeroImage}
	hideHeaderBrand
	hideHeaderSocial
	hideFooter
>
	<p>
		{app.name} is an AI-powered app built to help people explore ideas, draft content, and work
		through everyday questions with a clear, lightweight interface. This site collects the practical
		information users need after installing the app: what the app is for, how to get help, how
		subscriptions are managed, and where to review privacy and terms information.
	</p>

	<p>
		We design {app.name} around usefulness and transparency. AI output can be helpful, but it can
		also make mistakes, miss context, or sound more certain than it should. For that reason, the app
		is intended as a creative and productivity aid rather than a replacement for professional,
		medical, legal, financial, or safety-critical advice. Users should always review important
		results before relying on them.
	</p>

	<h2>What you can expect</h2>
	<p>
		Our goal is to keep the experience direct: quick access to AI assistance, plain-language support
		content, and straightforward guidance for account or subscription questions. If you purchased a
		subscription through the App Store, billing and cancellation are handled through your Apple ID
		subscription settings.
	</p>

	<h2>Support</h2>
	<p>
		For product questions, bug reports, or account support, email
		<a href={supportMailto}>{supportEmail}</a>. Include the app name, your device
		model, OS version, and a short description of the issue so we can investigate efficiently.
	</p>

	<h2>Privacy and policies</h2>
	<p>
		You can review the current policy pages for {app.name} at
		<a href={`/${app.slug}/privacy`}>Privacy Policy</a>,
		<a href={`/${app.slug}/terms`}>Terms of Use</a>, and
		<a href={`/${app.slug}/support`}>Support</a>. These pages are kept separate from marketing
		content so users can find operational details quickly.
	</p>
</Layout>
